  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "For the network architectures, we report them based on whether the network was used for feature extraction or for making a prediction.",
    "We start with the networks used for feature extraction.",
    "Xia et al. (2021) used the Autoencoder by Krizhevsky and Hinton (2011) to extract features from a dataset comprising 3,378 samples.",
    "The Autoencoder had an encoder composed of five fully connected layers, each with sizes of 675, 4,096, 2,048, 1,024, and 512 sequentially.",
    "This was followed by a bottleneck layer and, finally, a decoder that mirrored the encoder's structure but in reverse order."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Xia et al. (2021) used the Autoencoder by Krizhevsky and Hinton (2011) to extract features from a dataset comprising 3,378 samples."
  ]
}